75struct prefix_str {
76 size_t len;
77 char *str;
78 char is_prefix;
79};

81static void free_prefix_str(struct prefix_str *p)
82{
83 if (!p)
84 return;
85 free(p->str);
86}

88struct seapp_context {
89 /* input selectors */
90 bool isSystemServer;
91 bool isOwnerSet;
92 bool isOwner;
93 struct prefix_str user;
94 char *seinfo;
95 struct prefix_str name;
96 struct prefix_str path;
97 bool isPrivAppSet;
98 bool isPrivApp;
99 /* outputs */
100 char *domain;
101 char *type;
102 char *level;
103 enum levelFrom levelFrom;
104};
105
106static void free_seapp_context(struct seapp_context *s)
107{
108 if (!s)
109 return;
110
111 free_prefix_str(&s->user);
112 free(s->seinfo);
113 free_prefix_str(&s->name);
114 free_prefix_str(&s->path);
115 free(s->domain);
116 free(s->type);
117 free(s->level);
118}

120static bool seapp_contexts_dup = false;
121
122static int seapp_context_cmp(const void *A, const void *B)
123{
124 const struct seapp_context *const *sp1 = (const struct seapp_context *const *) A;
125 const struct seapp_context *const *sp2 = (const struct seapp_context *const *) B;
126 const struct seapp_context *s1 = *sp1, *s2 = *sp2;
127 bool dup;
128
129 /* Give precedence to isSystemServer=true. */
130 if (s1->isSystemServer != s2->isSystemServer)
131 return (s1->isSystemServer ? -1 : 1);
132
133 /* Give precedence to a specified isOwner= over an unspecified isOwner=. */
134 if (s1->isOwnerSet != s2->isOwnerSet)
135 return (s1->isOwnerSet ? -1 : 1);
136
137 /* Give precedence to a specified user= over an unspecified user=. */
138 if (s1->user.str && !s2->user.str)
139 return -1;
140 if (!s1->user.str && s2->user.str)
141 return 1;
142
143 if (s1->user.str) {
144 /* Give precedence to a fixed user= string over a prefix. */
145 if (s1->user.is_prefix != s2->user.is_prefix)
146 return (s2->user.is_prefix ? -1 : 1);
147
148 /* Give precedence to a longer prefix over a shorter prefix. */
149 if (s1->user.is_prefix && s1->user.len != s2->user.len)
150 return (s1->user.len > s2->user.len) ? -1 : 1;
151 }
152
153 /* Give precedence to a specified seinfo= over an unspecified seinfo=. */
154 if (s1->seinfo && !s2->seinfo)
155 return -1;
156 if (!s1->seinfo && s2->seinfo)
157 return 1;
158
159 /* Give precedence to a specified name= over an unspecified name=. */
160 if (s1->name.str && !s2->name.str)
161 return -1;
162 if (!s1->name.str && s2->name.str)
163 return 1;
164
165 if (s1->name.str) {
166 /* Give precedence to a fixed name= string over a prefix. */
167 if (s1->name.is_prefix != s2->name.is_prefix)
168 return (s2->name.is_prefix ? -1 : 1);
169
170 /* Give precedence to a longer prefix over a shorter prefix. */
171 if (s1->name.is_prefix && s1->name.len != s2->name.len)
172 return (s1->name.len > s2->name.len) ? -1 : 1;
173 }
174
175 /* Give precedence to a specified path= over an unspecified path=. */
176 if (s1->path.str && !s2->path.str)
177 return -1;
178 if (!s1->path.str && s2->path.str)
179 return 1;
180
181 if (s1->path.str) {
182 /* Give precedence to a fixed path= string over a prefix. */
183 if (s1->path.is_prefix != s2->path.is_prefix)
184 return (s2->path.is_prefix ? -1 : 1);
185
186 /* Give precedence to a longer prefix over a shorter prefix. */
187 if (s1->path.is_prefix && s1->path.len != s2->path.len)
188 return (s1->path.len > s2->path.len) ? -1 : 1;
189 }
190
191 /* Give precedence to a specified isPrivApp= over an unspecified isPrivApp=. */
192 if (s1->isPrivAppSet != s2->isPrivAppSet)
193 return (s1->isPrivAppSet ? -1 : 1);
194
195 /*
196 * Check for a duplicated entry on the input selectors.
197 * We already compared isSystemServer, isOwnerSet, and isOwner above.
198 * We also have already checked that both entries specify the same
199 * string fields, so if s1 has a non-NULL string, then so does s2.
200 */
201 dup = (!s1->user.str || !strcmp(s1->user.str, s2->user.str)) &&
202 (!s1->seinfo || !strcmp(s1->seinfo, s2->seinfo)) &&
203 (!s1->name.str || !strcmp(s1->name.str, s2->name.str)) &&
204 (!s1->path.str || !strcmp(s1->path.str, s2->path.str));
205 if (dup) {
206 seapp_contexts_dup = true;
207 selinux_log(SELINUX_ERROR, "seapp_contexts: Duplicated entry\n");
208 if (s1->user.str)
209 selinux_log(SELINUX_ERROR, " user=%s\n", s1->user.str);
210 if (s1->seinfo)
211 selinux_log(SELINUX_ERROR, " seinfo=%s\n", s1->seinfo);
212 if (s1->name.str)
213 selinux_log(SELINUX_ERROR, " name=%s\n", s1->name.str);
214 if (s1->path.str)
215 selinux_log(SELINUX_ERROR, " path=%s\n", s1->path.str);
216 }
217
218 /* Anything else has equal precedence. */
219 return 0;
220}
221
222static struct seapp_context **seapp_contexts = NULL;
223static int nspec = 0;
224
225static void free_seapp_contexts(void)
226{
227 int n;
228
229 if (!seapp_contexts)
230 return;
231
232 for (n = 0; n < nspec; n++)
233 free_seapp_context(seapp_contexts[n]);
234
235 free(seapp_contexts);
236 seapp_contexts = NULL;
237 nspec = 0;
238}

240int selinux_android_seapp_context_reload(void)
241{
242 FILE *fp = NULL;
243 char line_buf[BUFSIZ];
244 char *token;
245 unsigned lineno;
246 struct seapp_context *cur;
247 char *p, *name = NULL, *value = NULL, *saveptr;
248 size_t len;
249 int n, ret;
250
251 fp = fopen(seapp_contexts_file, "re");
252 if (!fp) {
253 selinux_log(SELINUX_ERROR, "%s: could not open any seapp_contexts file", __FUNCTION__);
254 return -1;
255 }
256
257 free_seapp_contexts();
258
259 nspec = 0;
260 while (fgets(line_buf, sizeof line_buf - 1, fp)) {
261 p = line_buf;
262 while (isspace(*p))
263 p++;
264 if (*p == '#' || *p == 0)
265 continue;
266 nspec++;
267 }
268
269 seapp_contexts = (struct seapp_context **) calloc(nspec, sizeof(struct seapp_context *));
270 if (!seapp_contexts)
271 goto oom;
272
273 rewind(fp);
274 nspec = 0;
275 lineno = 1;
276 while (fgets(line_buf, sizeof line_buf - 1, fp)) {
277 len = strlen(line_buf);
278 if (line_buf[len - 1] == '\n')
279 line_buf[len - 1] = 0;
280 p = line_buf;
281 while (isspace(*p))
282 p++;
283 if (*p == '#' || *p == 0)
284 continue;
285
286 cur = (struct seapp_context *) calloc(1, sizeof(struct seapp_context));
287 if (!cur)
288 goto oom;
289
290 token = strtok_r(p, " \t", &saveptr);
291 if (!token) {
292 free_seapp_context(cur);
293 goto err;
294 }
295
296 while (1) {
297 name = token;
298 value = strchr(name, '=');
299 if (!value) {
300 free_seapp_context(cur);
301 goto err;
302 }
303 *value++ = 0;
304
305 if (!strcasecmp(name, "isSystemServer")) {
306 if (!strcasecmp(value, "true"))
307 cur->isSystemServer = true;
308 else if (!strcasecmp(value, "false"))
309 cur->isSystemServer = false;
310 else {
311 free_seapp_context(cur);
312 goto err;
313 }
314 } else if (!strcasecmp(name, "isOwner")) {
315 cur->isOwnerSet = true;
316 if (!strcasecmp(value, "true"))
317 cur->isOwner = true;
318 else if (!strcasecmp(value, "false"))
319 cur->isOwner = false;
320 else {
321 free_seapp_context(cur);
322 goto err;
323 }
324 } else if (!strcasecmp(name, "user")) {
325 if (cur->user.str) {
326 free_seapp_context(cur);
327 goto err;
328 }
329 cur->user.str = strdup(value);
330 if (!cur->user.str) {
331 free_seapp_context(cur);
332 goto oom;
333 }
334 cur->user.len = strlen(cur->user.str);
335 if (cur->user.str[cur->user.len-1] == '*')
336 cur->user.is_prefix = 1;
337 } else if (!strcasecmp(name, "seinfo")) {
338 if (cur->seinfo) {
339 free_seapp_context(cur);
340 goto err;
341 }
342 cur->seinfo = strdup(value);
343 if (!cur->seinfo) {
344 free_seapp_context(cur);
345 goto oom;
346 }
347 if (strstr(value, ":")) {
348 free_seapp_context(cur);
349 goto err;
350 }
351 } else if (!strcasecmp(name, "name")) {
352 if (cur->name.str) {
353 free_seapp_context(cur);
354 goto err;
355 }
356 cur->name.str = strdup(value);
357 if (!cur->name.str) {
358 free_seapp_context(cur);
359 goto oom;
360 }
361 cur->name.len = strlen(cur->name.str);
362 if (cur->name.str[cur->name.len-1] == '*')
363 cur->name.is_prefix = 1;
364 } else if (!strcasecmp(name, "domain")) {
365 if (cur->domain) {
366 free_seapp_context(cur);
367 goto err;
368 }
369 cur->domain = strdup(value);
370 if (!cur->domain) {
371 free_seapp_context(cur);
372 goto oom;
373 }
374 } else if (!strcasecmp(name, "type")) {
375 if (cur->type) {
376 free_seapp_context(cur);
377 goto err;
378 }
379 cur->type = strdup(value);
380 if (!cur->type) {
381 free_seapp_context(cur);
382 goto oom;
383 }
384 } else if (!strcasecmp(name, "levelFromUid")) {
385 if (cur->levelFrom) {
386 free_seapp_context(cur);
387 goto err;
388 }
389 if (!strcasecmp(value, "true"))
390 cur->levelFrom = LEVELFROM_APP;
391 else if (!strcasecmp(value, "false"))
392 cur->levelFrom = LEVELFROM_NONE;
393 else {
394 free_seapp_context(cur);
395 goto err;
396 }
397 } else if (!strcasecmp(name, "levelFrom")) {
398 if (cur->levelFrom) {
399 free_seapp_context(cur);
400 goto err;
401 }
402 if (!strcasecmp(value, "none"))
403 cur->levelFrom = LEVELFROM_NONE;
404 else if (!strcasecmp(value, "app"))
405 cur->levelFrom = LEVELFROM_APP;
406 else if (!strcasecmp(value, "user"))
407 cur->levelFrom = LEVELFROM_USER;
408 else if (!strcasecmp(value, "all"))
409 cur->levelFrom = LEVELFROM_ALL;
410 else {
411 free_seapp_context(cur);
412 goto err;
413 }
414 } else if (!strcasecmp(name, "level")) {
415 if (cur->level) {
416 free_seapp_context(cur);
417 goto err;
418 }
419 cur->level = strdup(value);
420 if (!cur->level) {
421 free_seapp_context(cur);
422 goto oom;
423 }
424 } else if (!strcasecmp(name, "path")) {
425 if (cur->path.str) {
426 free_seapp_context(cur);
427 goto err;
428 }
429 cur->path.str = strdup(value);
430 if (!cur->path.str) {
431 free_seapp_context(cur);
432 goto oom;
433 }
434 cur->path.len = strlen(cur->path.str);
435 if (cur->path.str[cur->path.len-1] == '*')
436 cur->path.is_prefix = 1;
437 } else if (!strcasecmp(name, "isPrivApp")) {
438 cur->isPrivAppSet = true;
439 if (!strcasecmp(value, "true"))
440 cur->isPrivApp = true;
441 else if (!strcasecmp(value, "false"))
442 cur->isPrivApp = false;
443 else {
444 free_seapp_context(cur);
445 goto err;
446 }
447 } else {
448 free_seapp_context(cur);
449 goto err;
450 }
451
452 token = strtok_r(NULL, " \t", &saveptr);
453 if (!token)
454 break;
455 }
456
457 if (cur->name.str &&
458 (!cur->seinfo || !strcmp(cur->seinfo, "default"))) {
459 selinux_log(SELINUX_ERROR, "%s: No specific seinfo value specified with name=\"%s\", on line %u: insecure configuration!\n",
460 seapp_contexts_file, cur->name.str, lineno);
461 free_seapp_context(cur);
462 goto err;
463 }
464
465 seapp_contexts[nspec] = cur;
466 nspec++;
467 lineno++;
468 }
469
470 qsort(seapp_contexts, nspec, sizeof(struct seapp_context *),
471 seapp_context_cmp);
472
473 if (seapp_contexts_dup)
474 goto err;
475
476#if DEBUG
477 {
478 int i;
479 for (i = 0; i < nspec; i++) {
480 cur = seapp_contexts[i];
481 selinux_log(SELINUX_INFO, "%s: isSystemServer=%s isOwner=%s user=%s seinfo=%s name=%s path=%s isPrivApp=%s -> domain=%s type=%s level=%s levelFrom=%s",
482 __FUNCTION__,
483 cur->isSystemServer ? "true" : "false",
484 cur->isOwnerSet ? (cur->isOwner ? "true" : "false") : "null",
485 cur->user.str,
486 cur->seinfo, cur->name.str, cur->path.str,
487 cur->isPrivAppSet ? (cur->isPrivApp ? "true" : "false") : "null",
488 cur->domain, cur->type, cur->level,
489 levelFromName[cur->levelFrom]);
490 }
491 }
492#endif
493
494 ret = 0;
495
496out:
497 fclose(fp);
498 return ret;
499
500err:
501 selinux_log(SELINUX_ERROR, "%s: Invalid entry on line %u\n",
502 seapp_contexts_file, lineno);
503 free_seapp_contexts();
504 ret = -1;
505 goto out;
506oom:
507 selinux_log(SELINUX_ERROR,
508 "%s: Out of memory\n", __FUNCTION__);
509 free_seapp_contexts();
510 ret = -1;
511 goto out;
512}

517 selinux_android_seapp_context_reload();

520static pthread_once_t once = PTHREAD_ONCE_INIT;
521
522/*
523 * Max id that can be mapped to category set uniquely
524 * using the current scheme.
525 */
526#define CAT_MAPPING_MAX_ID (0x1<<16)
527
528enum seapp_kind {
529 SEAPP_TYPE,
530 SEAPP_DOMAIN
531};
532
533#define PRIVILEGED_APP_STR ":privapp"
534static bool is_app_privileged(const char *seinfo)
535{
536 return strstr(seinfo, PRIVILEGED_APP_STR) != NULL;
537}
538
539static int seinfo_parse(char *dest, const char *src, size_t size)
540{
541 size_t len;
542 char *p;
543
544 if ((p = strchr(src, ':')) != NULL)
545 len = p - src;
546 else
547 len = strlen(src);
548
549 if (len > size - 1)
550 return -1;
551
552 strncpy(dest, src, len);
553 dest[len] = '\0';
554
555 return 0;
556}
557
558static int seapp_context_lookup(enum seapp_kind kind,
559 uid_t uid,
560 bool isSystemServer,
561 const char *seinfo,
562 const char *pkgname,
563 const char *path,
564 context_t ctx)
565{
566 bool isOwner;
567 const char *username = NULL;
568 struct seapp_context *cur = NULL;
569 int i;
570 size_t n;
571 uid_t userid;
572 uid_t appid;
573 bool isPrivApp = false;
574 char parsedseinfo[BUFSIZ];
575
576 __selinux_once(once, seapp_context_init);
577
578 if (seinfo) {
579 if (seinfo_parse(parsedseinfo, seinfo, BUFSIZ))
580 goto err;
581 isPrivApp = is_app_privileged(seinfo);
582 seinfo = parsedseinfo;
583 }
584
585 userid = uid / AID_USER;
586 isOwner = (userid == 0);
587 appid = uid % AID_USER;
588 if (appid < AID_APP) {
589 for (n = 0; n < android_id_count; n++) {
590 if (android_ids[n].aid == appid) {
591 username = android_ids[n].name;
592 break;
593 }
594 }
595 if (!username)
596 goto err;
597 } else if (appid < AID_ISOLATED_START) {
598 username = "_app";
599 appid -= AID_APP;
600 } else {
601 username = "_isolated";
602 appid -= AID_ISOLATED_START;
603 }
604
605 if (appid >= CAT_MAPPING_MAX_ID || userid >= CAT_MAPPING_MAX_ID)
606 goto err;
607
608 for (i = 0; i < nspec; i++) {
609 cur = seapp_contexts[i];
610
611 if (cur->isSystemServer != isSystemServer)
612 continue;
613
614 if (cur->isOwnerSet && cur->isOwner != isOwner)
615 continue;
616
617 if (cur->user.str) {
618 if (cur->user.is_prefix) {
619 if (strncasecmp(username, cur->user.str, cur->user.len-1))
620 continue;
621 } else {
622 if (strcasecmp(username, cur->user.str))
623 continue;
624 }
625 }
626
627 if (cur->seinfo) {
628 if (!seinfo || strcasecmp(seinfo, cur->seinfo))
629 continue;
630 }
631
632 if (cur->name.str) {
633 if(!pkgname)
634 continue;
635
636 if (cur->name.is_prefix) {
637 if (strncasecmp(pkgname, cur->name.str, cur->name.len-1))
638 continue;
639 } else {
640 if (strcasecmp(pkgname, cur->name.str))
641 continue;
642 }
643 }
644
645 if (cur->isPrivAppSet && cur->isPrivApp != isPrivApp)
646 continue;
647
648 if (cur->path.str) {
649 if (!path)
650 continue;
651
652 if (cur->path.is_prefix) {
653 if (strncmp(path, cur->path.str, cur->path.len-1))
654 continue;
655 } else {
656 if (strcmp(path, cur->path.str))
657 continue;
658 }
659 }
660
661 if (kind == SEAPP_TYPE && !cur->type)
662 continue;
663 else if (kind == SEAPP_DOMAIN && !cur->domain)
664 continue;
665
666 if (kind == SEAPP_TYPE) {
667 if (context_type_set(ctx, cur->type))
668 goto oom;
669 } else if (kind == SEAPP_DOMAIN) {
670 if (context_type_set(ctx, cur->domain))
671 goto oom;
672 }
673
674 if (cur->levelFrom != LEVELFROM_NONE) {
675 char level[255];
676 switch (cur->levelFrom) {
677 case LEVELFROM_APP:
678 snprintf(level, sizeof level, "s0:c%u,c%u",
679 appid & 0xff,
680 256 + (appid>>8 & 0xff));
681 break;
682 case LEVELFROM_USER:
683 snprintf(level, sizeof level, "s0:c%u,c%u",
684 512 + (userid & 0xff),
685 768 + (userid>>8 & 0xff));
686 break;
687 case LEVELFROM_ALL:
688 snprintf(level, sizeof level, "s0:c%u,c%u,c%u,c%u",
689 appid & 0xff,
690 256 + (appid>>8 & 0xff),
691 512 + (userid & 0xff),
692 768 + (userid>>8 & 0xff));
693 break;
694 default:
695 goto err;
696 }
697 if (context_range_set(ctx, level))
698 goto oom;
699 } else if (cur->level) {
700 if (context_range_set(ctx, cur->level))
701 goto oom;
702 }
703
704 break;
705 }
706
707 if (kind == SEAPP_DOMAIN && i == nspec) {
708 /*
709 * No match.
710 * Fail to prevent staying in the zygote's context.
711 */
712 selinux_log(SELINUX_ERROR,
713 "%s: No match for app with uid %d, seinfo %s, name %s\n",
714 __FUNCTION__, uid, seinfo, pkgname);
715
716 if (security_getenforce() == 1)
717 goto err;
718 }
719
720 return 0;
721err:
722 return -1;
723oom:
724 return -2;
725}
726
727int selinux_android_setfilecon(const char *pkgdir,
728 const char *pkgname,
729 const char *seinfo,
730 uid_t uid)
731{
732 char *orig_ctx_str = NULL;
733 char *ctx_str = NULL;
734 context_t ctx = NULL;
735 int rc = -1;
736
737 if (is_selinux_enabled() <= 0)
738 return 0;
739
740 rc = getfilecon(pkgdir, &ctx_str);
741 if (rc < 0)
742 goto err;
743
744 ctx = context_new(ctx_str);
745 orig_ctx_str = ctx_str;
746 if (!ctx)
747 goto oom;
748
749 rc = seapp_context_lookup(SEAPP_TYPE, uid, 0, seinfo, pkgname, NULL, ctx);
750 if (rc == -1)
751 goto err;
752 else if (rc == -2)
753 goto oom;
754
755 ctx_str = context_str(ctx);
756 if (!ctx_str)
757 goto oom;
758
759 rc = security_check_context(ctx_str);
760 if (rc < 0)
761 goto err;
762
763 if (strcmp(ctx_str, orig_ctx_str)) {
764 rc = setfilecon(pkgdir, ctx_str);
765 if (rc < 0)
766 goto err;
767 }
768
769 rc = 0;
770out:
771 freecon(orig_ctx_str);
772 context_free(ctx);
773 return rc;
774err:
775 selinux_log(SELINUX_ERROR, "%s: Error setting context for pkgdir %s, uid %d: %s\n",
776 __FUNCTION__, pkgdir, uid, strerror(errno));
777 rc = -1;
778 goto out;
779oom:
780 selinux_log(SELINUX_ERROR, "%s: Out of memory\n", __FUNCTION__);
781 rc = -1;
782 goto out;
783}
784
785int selinux_android_setcon(const char *con)
786{
787 int ret = setcon(con);
788 if (ret)
789 return ret;
790 /*
791 System properties must be reinitialized after setcon() otherwise the
792 previous property files will be leaked since mmap()'ed regions are not
793 closed as a result of setcon().
794 */
795 return __system_properties_init();
796}
797
798int selinux_android_setcontext(uid_t uid,
799 bool isSystemServer,
800 const char *seinfo,
801 const char *pkgname)
802{
803 char *orig_ctx_str = NULL, *ctx_str;
804 context_t ctx = NULL;
805 int rc = -1;
806
807 if (is_selinux_enabled() <= 0)
808 return 0;
809
810 rc = getcon(&ctx_str);
811 if (rc)
812 goto err;
813
814 ctx = context_new(ctx_str);
815 orig_ctx_str = ctx_str;
816 if (!ctx)
817 goto oom;
818
819 rc = seapp_context_lookup(SEAPP_DOMAIN, uid, isSystemServer, seinfo, pkgname, NULL, ctx);
820 if (rc == -1)
821 goto err;
822 else if (rc == -2)
823 goto oom;
824
825 ctx_str = context_str(ctx);
826 if (!ctx_str)
827 goto oom;
828
829 rc = security_check_context(ctx_str);
830 if (rc < 0)
831 goto err;
832
833 if (strcmp(ctx_str, orig_ctx_str)) {
834 rc = selinux_android_setcon(ctx_str);
835 if (rc < 0)
836 goto err;
837 }
838
839 rc = 0;
840out:
841 freecon(orig_ctx_str);
842 context_free(ctx);
843 avc_netlink_close();
844 return rc;
845err:
846 if (isSystemServer)
847 selinux_log(SELINUX_ERROR,
848 "%s: Error setting context for system server: %s\n",
849 __FUNCTION__, strerror(errno));
850 else
851 selinux_log(SELINUX_ERROR,
852 "%s: Error setting context for app with uid %d, seinfo %s: %s\n",
853 __FUNCTION__, uid, seinfo, strerror(errno));
854
855 rc = -1;
856 goto out;
857oom:
858 selinux_log(SELINUX_ERROR, "%s: Out of memory\n", __FUNCTION__);
859 rc = -1;
860 goto out;
861}
862
863static struct selabel_handle *fc_sehandle = NULL;
864#define FC_DIGEST_SIZE SHA_DIGEST_LENGTH
865static uint8_t fc_digest[FC_DIGEST_SIZE];
866
867static bool compute_file_contexts_hash(uint8_t c_digest[])
868{
869 int fd;
870 struct stat sb;
871 void *map;
872
873 fd = open(seopts.value, O_CLOEXEC | O_RDONLY | O_NOFOLLOW);
874 if (fd < 0) {
875 selinux_log(SELINUX_ERROR, "SELinux: Could not open %s: %s\n",
876 seopts.value, strerror(errno));
877 return false;
878 }
879 if (fstat(fd, &sb) < 0) {
880 selinux_log(SELINUX_ERROR, "SELinux: Could not stat %s: %s\n",
881 seopts.value, strerror(errno));
882 close(fd);
883 return false;
884 }
885 map = mmap(NULL, sb.st_size, PROT_READ, MAP_PRIVATE, fd, 0);
886 if (map == MAP_FAILED) {
887 selinux_log(SELINUX_ERROR, "SELinux: Could not map %s: %s\n",
888 seopts.value, strerror(errno));
889 close(fd);
890 return false;
891 }
892 SHA1(map, sb.st_size, c_digest);
893 munmap(map, sb.st_size);
894 close(fd);
895
896 return true;
897}
898
899static void file_context_init(void)
900{
901 if (!fc_sehandle)
902 fc_sehandle = selinux_android_file_context_handle();
903}

906
907static pthread_once_t fc_once = PTHREAD_ONCE_INIT;
908
909#define PKGTAB_SIZE 256
910static struct pkg_info *pkgTab[PKGTAB_SIZE];
911
912static unsigned int pkghash(const char *pkgname)
913{
914 unsigned int h = 7;
915 for (; *pkgname; pkgname++) {
916 h = h * 31 + *pkgname;
917 }
918 return h & (PKGTAB_SIZE - 1);
919}
920
921static bool pkg_parse_callback(pkg_info *info, void *userdata) {
922
923 (void) userdata;
924
925 unsigned int hash = pkghash(info->name);
926 if (pkgTab[hash])
927 info->private_data = pkgTab[hash];
928 pkgTab[hash] = info;
929 return true;
930}
931
932static void package_info_init(void)
933{
934
935 bool rc = packagelist_parse(pkg_parse_callback, NULL);
936 if (!rc) {
937 selinux_log(SELINUX_ERROR, "SELinux: Could NOT parse package list\n");
938 return;
939 }
940
941#if DEBUG
942 {
943 unsigned int hash, buckets, entries, chainlen, longestchain;
944 struct pkg_info *info = NULL;
945
946 buckets = entries = longestchain = 0;
947 for (hash = 0; hash < PKGTAB_SIZE; hash++) {
948 if (pkgTab[hash]) {
949 buckets++;
950 chainlen = 0;
951 for (info = pkgTab[hash]; info; info = (pkg_info *)info->private_data) {
952 chainlen++;
953 selinux_log(SELINUX_INFO, "%s: name=%s uid=%u debuggable=%s dataDir=%s seinfo=%s\n",
954 __FUNCTION__,
955 info->name, info->uid, info->debuggable ? "true" : "false", info->data_dir, info->seinfo);
956 }
957 entries += chainlen;
958 if (longestchain < chainlen)
959 longestchain = chainlen;
960 }
961 }
962 selinux_log(SELINUX_INFO, "SELinux: %d pkg entries and %d/%d buckets used, longest chain %d\n", entries, buckets, PKGTAB_SIZE, longestchain);
963 }
964#endif
965
966}
967
968static pthread_once_t pkg_once = PTHREAD_ONCE_INIT;
969
970struct pkg_info *package_info_lookup(const char *name)
971{
972 struct pkg_info *info;
973 unsigned int hash;
974
975 __selinux_once(pkg_once, package_info_init);
976
977 hash = pkghash(name);
978 for (info = pkgTab[hash]; info; info = (pkg_info *)info->private_data) {
979 if (!strcmp(name, info->name))
980 return info;
981 }
982 return NULL;
983}
984
985/* The path prefixes of package data directories. */
986#define DATA_DATA_PATH "/data/data"
987#define DATA_USER_PATH "/data/user"
988#define DATA_USER_DE_PATH "/data/user_de"
989#define EXPAND_USER_PATH "/mnt/expand/\?\?\?\?\?\?\?\?-\?\?\?\?-\?\?\?\?-\?\?\?\?-\?\?\?\?\?\?\?\?\?\?\?\?/user"
990#define EXPAND_USER_DE_PATH "/mnt/expand/\?\?\?\?\?\?\?\?-\?\?\?\?-\?\?\?\?-\?\?\?\?-\?\?\?\?\?\?\?\?\?\?\?\?/user_de"
991#define DATA_DATA_PREFIX DATA_DATA_PATH "/"
992#define DATA_USER_PREFIX DATA_USER_PATH "/"
993#define DATA_USER_DE_PREFIX DATA_USER_DE_PATH "/"
994
995static int pkgdir_selabel_lookup(const char *pathname,
996 const char *seinfo,
997 uid_t uid,
998 char **secontextp)
999{
1000 char *pkgname = NULL, *end = NULL;
1001 struct pkg_info *info = NULL;
1002 char *secontext = *secontextp;
1003 context_t ctx = NULL;
1004 int rc = 0;
1005
1006 /* Skip directory prefix before package name. */
1007 if (!strncmp(pathname, DATA_DATA_PREFIX, sizeof(DATA_DATA_PREFIX)-1)) {
1008 pathname += sizeof(DATA_DATA_PREFIX) - 1;
1009 } else if (!strncmp(pathname, DATA_USER_PREFIX, sizeof(DATA_USER_PREFIX)-1)) {
1010 pathname += sizeof(DATA_USER_PREFIX) - 1;
1011 while (isdigit(*pathname))
1012 pathname++;
1013 if (*pathname == '/')
1014 pathname++;
1015 else
1016 return 0;
1017 } else if (!strncmp(pathname, DATA_USER_DE_PREFIX, sizeof(DATA_USER_DE_PREFIX)-1)) {
1018 pathname += sizeof(DATA_USER_DE_PREFIX) - 1;
1019 while (isdigit(*pathname))
1020 pathname++;
1021 if (*pathname == '/')
1022 pathname++;
1023 else
1024 return 0;
1025 } else if (!fnmatch(EXPAND_USER_PATH, pathname, FNM_LEADING_DIR|FNM_PATHNAME)) {
1026 pathname += sizeof(EXPAND_USER_PATH);
1027 while (isdigit(*pathname))
1028 pathname++;
1029 if (*pathname == '/')
1030 pathname++;
1031 else
1032 return 0;
1033 } else if (!fnmatch(EXPAND_USER_DE_PATH, pathname, FNM_LEADING_DIR|FNM_PATHNAME)) {
1034 pathname += sizeof(EXPAND_USER_DE_PATH);
1035 while (isdigit(*pathname))
1036 pathname++;
1037 if (*pathname == '/')
1038 pathname++;
1039 else
1040 return 0;
1041 } else
1042 return 0;
1043
1044 if (!(*pathname))
1045 return 0;
1046
1047 pkgname = strdup(pathname);
1048 if (!pkgname)
1049 return -1;
1050
1051 for (end = pkgname; *end && *end != '/'; end++)
1052 ;
1053 pathname = end;
1054 if (*end)
1055 pathname++;
1056 *end = '\0';
1057
1058 if (!seinfo) {
1059 info = package_info_lookup(pkgname);
1060 if (!info) {
1061 selinux_log(SELINUX_WARNING, "SELinux: Could not look up information for package %s, cannot restorecon %s.\n",
1062 pkgname, pathname);
1063 free(pkgname);
1064 return -1;
1065 }
1066 }
1067
1068 ctx = context_new(secontext);
1069 if (!ctx)
1070 goto err;
1071
1072 rc = seapp_context_lookup(SEAPP_TYPE, info ? info->uid : uid, 0,
1073 info ? info->seinfo : seinfo, info ? info->name : pkgname, pathname, ctx);
1074 if (rc < 0)
1075 goto err;
1076
1077 secontext = context_str(ctx);
1078 if (!secontext)
1079 goto err;
1080
1081 if (!strcmp(secontext, *secontextp))
1082 goto out;
1083
1084 rc = security_check_context(secontext);
1085 if (rc < 0)
1086 goto err;
1087
1088 freecon(*secontextp);
1089 *secontextp = strdup(secontext);
1090 if (!(*secontextp))
1091 goto err;
1092
1093 rc = 0;
1094
1095out:
1096 free(pkgname);
1097 context_free(ctx);
1098 return rc;
1099err:
1100 selinux_log(SELINUX_ERROR, "%s: Error looking up context for path %s, pkgname %s, seinfo %s, uid %u: %s\n",
1101 __FUNCTION__, pathname, pkgname, info->seinfo, info->uid, strerror(errno));
1102 rc = -1;
1103 goto out;
1104}
1105
1106#define RESTORECON_LAST "security.restorecon_last"
1107
1108static int restorecon_sb(const char *pathname, const struct stat *sb,
1109 bool nochange, bool verbose,
1110 const char *seinfo, uid_t uid)
1111{
1112 char *secontext = NULL;
1113 char *oldsecontext = NULL;
1114 int rc = 0;
1115
1116 if (selabel_lookup(fc_sehandle, &secontext, pathname, sb->st_mode) < 0)
1117 return 0; /* no match, but not an error */
1118
1119 if (lgetfilecon(pathname, &oldsecontext) < 0)
1120 goto err;
1121
1122 /*
1123 * For subdirectories of /data/data or /data/user, we ignore selabel_lookup()
1124 * and use pkgdir_selabel_lookup() instead. Files within those directories
1125 * have different labeling rules, based off of /seapp_contexts, and
1126 * installd is responsible for managing these labels instead of init.
1127 */
1128 if (!strncmp(pathname, DATA_DATA_PREFIX, sizeof(DATA_DATA_PREFIX)-1) ||
1129 !strncmp(pathname, DATA_USER_PREFIX, sizeof(DATA_USER_PREFIX)-1) ||
1130 !strncmp(pathname, DATA_USER_DE_PREFIX, sizeof(DATA_USER_DE_PREFIX)-1) ||
1131 !fnmatch(EXPAND_USER_PATH, pathname, FNM_LEADING_DIR|FNM_PATHNAME) ||
1132 !fnmatch(EXPAND_USER_DE_PATH, pathname, FNM_LEADING_DIR|FNM_PATHNAME)) {
1133 if (pkgdir_selabel_lookup(pathname, seinfo, uid, &secontext) < 0)
1134 goto err;
1135 }
1136
1137 if (strcmp(oldsecontext, secontext) != 0) {
1138 if (verbose)
1139 selinux_log(SELINUX_INFO,
1140 "SELinux: Relabeling %s from %s to %s.\n", pathname, oldsecontext, secontext);
1141 if (!nochange) {
1142 if (lsetfilecon(pathname, secontext) < 0)
1143 goto err;
1144 }
1145 }
1146
1147 rc = 0;
1148
1149out:
1150 freecon(oldsecontext);
1151 freecon(secontext);
1152 return rc;
1153
1154err:
1155 selinux_log(SELINUX_ERROR,
1156 "SELinux: Could not set context for %s: %s\n",
1157 pathname, strerror(errno));
1158 rc = -1;
1159 goto out;
1160}
1161
1162#define SYS_PATH "/sys"
1163#define SYS_PREFIX SYS_PATH "/"
1164
1165static int selinux_android_restorecon_common(const char* pathname_orig,
1166 const char *seinfo,
1167 uid_t uid,
1168 unsigned int flags)
1169{
1170 bool nochange = (flags & SELINUX_ANDROID_RESTORECON_NOCHANGE) ? true : false;
1171 bool verbose = (flags & SELINUX_ANDROID_RESTORECON_VERBOSE) ? true : false;
1172 bool recurse = (flags & SELINUX_ANDROID_RESTORECON_RECURSE) ? true : false;
1173 bool force = (flags & SELINUX_ANDROID_RESTORECON_FORCE) ? true : false;
1174 bool datadata = (flags & SELINUX_ANDROID_RESTORECON_DATADATA) ? true : false;
1175 bool issys;
1176 bool setrestoreconlast = true;
1177 struct stat sb;
1178 struct statfs sfsb;
1179 FTS *fts;
1180 FTSENT *ftsent;
1181 char *pathname = NULL, *pathdnamer = NULL, *pathdname, *pathbname;
1182 char * paths[2] = { NULL , NULL };
1183 int ftsflags = FTS_NOCHDIR | FTS_XDEV | FTS_PHYSICAL;
1184 int error, sverrno;
1185 char xattr_value[FC_DIGEST_SIZE];
1186 ssize_t size;
1187
1188 if (is_selinux_enabled() <= 0)
1189 return 0;
1190
1191 __selinux_once(fc_once, file_context_init);
1192
1193 if (!fc_sehandle)
1194 return 0;
1195
1196 /*
1197 * Convert passed-in pathname to canonical pathname by resolving realpath of
1198 * containing dir, then appending last component name.
1199 */
1200 pathbname = basename(pathname_orig);
1201 if (!strcmp(pathbname, "/") || !strcmp(pathbname, ".") || !strcmp(pathbname, "..")) {
1202 pathname = realpath(pathname_orig, NULL);
1203 if (!pathname)
1204 goto realpatherr;
1205 } else {
1206 pathdname = dirname(pathname_orig);
1207 pathdnamer = realpath(pathdname, NULL);
1208 if (!pathdnamer)
1209 goto realpatherr;
1210 if (!strcmp(pathdnamer, "/"))
1211 error = asprintf(&pathname, "/%s", pathbname);
1212 else
1213 error = asprintf(&pathname, "%s/%s", pathdnamer, pathbname);
1214 if (error < 0)
1215 goto oom;
1216 }
1217
1218 paths[0] = pathname;
1219 issys = (!strcmp(pathname, SYS_PATH)
1220 || !strncmp(pathname, SYS_PREFIX, sizeof(SYS_PREFIX)-1)) ? true : false;
1221
1222 if (!recurse) {
1223 if (lstat(pathname, &sb) < 0) {
1224 error = -1;
1225 goto cleanup;
1226 }
1227
1228 error = restorecon_sb(pathname, &sb, nochange, verbose, seinfo, uid);
1229 goto cleanup;
1230 }
1231
1232 /*
1233 * Ignore restorecon_last on /data/data or /data/user
1234 * since their labeling is based on seapp_contexts and seinfo
1235 * assignments rather than file_contexts and is managed by
1236 * installd rather than init.
1237 */
1238 if (!strncmp(pathname, DATA_DATA_PREFIX, sizeof(DATA_DATA_PREFIX)-1) ||
1239 !strncmp(pathname, DATA_USER_PREFIX, sizeof(DATA_USER_PREFIX)-1) ||
1240 !strncmp(pathname, DATA_USER_DE_PREFIX, sizeof(DATA_USER_DE_PREFIX)-1) ||
1241 !fnmatch(EXPAND_USER_PATH, pathname, FNM_LEADING_DIR|FNM_PATHNAME) ||
1242 !fnmatch(EXPAND_USER_DE_PATH, pathname, FNM_LEADING_DIR|FNM_PATHNAME))
1243 setrestoreconlast = false;
1244
1245 /* Also ignore on /sys since it is regenerated on each boot regardless. */
1246 if (issys)
1247 setrestoreconlast = false;
1248
1249 /* Ignore files on in-memory filesystems */
1250 if (statfs(pathname, &sfsb) == 0) {
1251 if (sfsb.f_type == RAMFS_MAGIC || sfsb.f_type == TMPFS_MAGIC)
1252 setrestoreconlast = false;
1253 }
1254
1255 if (setrestoreconlast) {
1256 size = getxattr(pathname, RESTORECON_LAST, xattr_value, sizeof fc_digest);
1257 if (!force && size == sizeof fc_digest && memcmp(fc_digest, xattr_value, sizeof fc_digest) == 0) {
1258 selinux_log(SELINUX_INFO,
1259 "SELinux: Skipping restorecon_recursive(%s)\n",
1260 pathname);
1261 error = 0;
1262 goto cleanup;
1263 }
1264 }
1265
1266 fts = fts_open(paths, ftsflags, NULL);
1267 if (!fts) {
1268 error = -1;
1269 goto cleanup;
1270 }
1271
1272 error = 0;
1273 while ((ftsent = fts_read(fts)) != NULL) {
1274 switch (ftsent->fts_info) {
1275 case FTS_DC:
1276 selinux_log(SELINUX_ERROR,
1277 "SELinux: Directory cycle on %s.\n", ftsent->fts_path);
1278 errno = ELOOP;
1279 error = -1;
1280 goto out;
1281 case FTS_DP:
1282 continue;
1283 case FTS_DNR:
1284 selinux_log(SELINUX_ERROR,
1285 "SELinux: Could not read %s: %s.\n", ftsent->fts_path, strerror(errno));
1286 fts_set(fts, ftsent, FTS_SKIP);
1287 continue;
1288 case FTS_NS:
1289 selinux_log(SELINUX_ERROR,
1290 "SELinux: Could not stat %s: %s.\n", ftsent->fts_path, strerror(errno));
1291 fts_set(fts, ftsent, FTS_SKIP);
1292 continue;
1293 case FTS_ERR:
1294 selinux_log(SELINUX_ERROR,
1295 "SELinux: Error on %s: %s.\n", ftsent->fts_path, strerror(errno));
1296 fts_set(fts, ftsent, FTS_SKIP);
1297 continue;
1298 case FTS_D:
1299 if (issys && !selabel_partial_match(fc_sehandle, ftsent->fts_path)) {
1300 fts_set(fts, ftsent, FTS_SKIP);
1301 continue;
1302 }
1303
1304 if (!datadata &&
1305 (!strcmp(ftsent->fts_path, DATA_DATA_PATH) ||
1306 !strncmp(ftsent->fts_path, DATA_USER_PREFIX, sizeof(DATA_USER_PREFIX)-1) ||
1307 !strncmp(ftsent->fts_path, DATA_USER_DE_PREFIX, sizeof(DATA_USER_DE_PREFIX)-1) ||
1308 !fnmatch(EXPAND_USER_PATH, ftsent->fts_path, FNM_LEADING_DIR|FNM_PATHNAME) ||
1309 !fnmatch(EXPAND_USER_DE_PATH, ftsent->fts_path, FNM_LEADING_DIR|FNM_PATHNAME))) {
1310 // Don't label anything below this directory.
1311 fts_set(fts, ftsent, FTS_SKIP);
1312 // but fall through and make sure we label the directory itself
1313 }
1314 /* fall through */
1315 default:
1316 error |= restorecon_sb(ftsent->fts_path, ftsent->fts_statp, nochange, verbose, seinfo, uid);
1317 break;
1318 }
1319 }
1320
1321 // Labeling successful. Mark the top level directory as completed.
1322 if (setrestoreconlast && !nochange && !error)
1323 setxattr(pathname, RESTORECON_LAST, fc_digest, sizeof fc_digest, 0);
1324
1325out:
1326 sverrno = errno;
1327 (void) fts_close(fts);
1328 errno = sverrno;
1329cleanup:
1330 free(pathdnamer);
1331 free(pathname);
1332 return error;
1333oom:
1334 sverrno = errno;
1335 selinux_log(SELINUX_ERROR, "%s: Out of memory\n", __FUNCTION__);
1336 errno = sverrno;
1337 error = -1;
1338 goto cleanup;
1339realpatherr:
1340 sverrno = errno;
1341 selinux_log(SELINUX_ERROR, "SELinux: Could not get canonical path for %s restorecon: %s.\n",
1342 pathname_orig, strerror(errno));
1343 errno = sverrno;
1344 error = -1;
1345 goto cleanup;
1346}
1347
1348int selinux_android_restorecon(const char *file, unsigned int flags)
1349{
1350 return selinux_android_restorecon_common(file, NULL, -1, flags);
1351}

1361struct selabel_handle* selinux_android_file_context_handle(void)
1362{
1363 char *path = NULL;
1364 struct selabel_handle *sehandle;
1365 struct selinux_opt fc_opts[] = {
1366 { SELABEL_OPT_PATH, path },
1367 { SELABEL_OPT_BASEONLY, (char *)1 }
1368 };
1369
1370 fc_opts[0].value = seopts.value;
1371
1372 sehandle = selabel_open(SELABEL_CTX_FILE, fc_opts, 2);
1373
1374 if (!sehandle) {
1375 selinux_log(SELINUX_ERROR, "%s: Error getting file context handle (%s)\n",
1376 __FUNCTION__, strerror(errno));
1377 return NULL;
1378 }
1379 if (!compute_file_contexts_hash(fc_digest)) {
1380 selabel_close(sehandle);
1381 return NULL;
1382 }
1383 selinux_log(SELINUX_INFO, "SELinux: Loaded file_contexts contexts from %s.\n",
1384 fc_opts[0].value);
1385
1386 return sehandle;
1387}

1428
1429int selinux_android_load_policy(void)
1430{
1431 int fd = -1, rc;
1432 struct stat sb;
1433 void *map = NULL;
1434 static int load_successful = 0;
1435
1436 /*
1437 * Since updating policy at runtime has been abolished
1438 * we just check whether a policy has been loaded before
1439 * and return if this is the case.
1440 * There is no point in reloading policy.
1441 */
1442 if (load_successful){
1443 selinux_log(SELINUX_WARNING, "SELinux: Attempted reload of SELinux policy!/n");
1444 return 0;
1445 }
1446
1447 set_selinuxmnt(SELINUXMNT);
1448 fd = open(sepolicy_file, O_RDONLY | O_NOFOLLOW | O_CLOEXEC);
1449 if (fd < 0) {
1450 selinux_log(SELINUX_ERROR, "SELinux: Could not open sepolicy: %s\n",
1451 strerror(errno));
1452 return -1;
1453 }
1454 if (fstat(fd, &sb) < 0) {
1455 selinux_log(SELINUX_ERROR, "SELinux: Could not stat %s: %s\n",
1456 sepolicy_file, strerror(errno));
1457 close(fd);
1458 return -1;
1459 }
1460 map = mmap(NULL, sb.st_size, PROT_READ, MAP_PRIVATE, fd, 0);
1461 if (map == MAP_FAILED) {
1462 selinux_log(SELINUX_ERROR, "SELinux: Could not map %s: %s\n",
1463 sepolicy_file, strerror(errno));
1464 close(fd);
1465 return -1;
1466 }
1467
1468 rc = security_load_policy(map, sb.st_size);
1469 if (rc < 0) {
1470 selinux_log(SELINUX_ERROR, "SELinux: Could not load policy: %s\n",
1471 strerror(errno));
1472 munmap(map, sb.st_size);
1473 close(fd);
1474 return -1;
1475 }
1476
1477 munmap(map, sb.st_size);
1478 close(fd);
1479 selinux_log(SELINUX_INFO, "SELinux: Loaded policy from %s\n", sepolicy_file);
1480 load_successful = 1;
1481 return 0;
1482}
1483
1484int selinux_log_callback(int type, const char *fmt, ...)
1485{
1486 va_list ap;
1487 int priority;
1488 char *strp;
1489
1490 switch(type) {
1491 case SELINUX_WARNING:
1492 priority = ANDROID_LOG_WARN;
1493 break;
1494 case SELINUX_INFO:
1495 priority = ANDROID_LOG_INFO;
1496 break;
1497 default:
1498 priority = ANDROID_LOG_ERROR;
1499 break;
1500 }
1501
1502 va_start(ap, fmt);
1503 if (vasprintf(&strp, fmt, ap) != -1) {
1504 LOG_PRI(priority, "SELinux", "%s", strp);
1505 LOG_EVENT_STRING(AUDITD_LOG_TAG, strp);
1506 free(strp);
1507 }
1508 va_end(ap);
1509 return 0;
1510}
